pageContext.claim: “Automobile sales, likewise, are a key factor in the resurgence of manufacturing since the March low of 8.8 million units with sales and all of the numbers that are going up, stunningly. It's a 65 percent increase since then, to 14.5 million units, which is a -- a massive number... Record-setting numbers.”
pageContext.analysis: Like many of the economic statistics that Trump has touted he neglects to mention why there was a decline in March and April. Moreover, although car sales have pushed up, they have not returned to pre-pandemic levels.
